      • toIterator

        public static <T> java.util.Iterator<T> toIterator(java.lang.Object o)
        Map iterables and arrays to iterators or returns null. If an iterator is passed it, it is returned. This will not wrap a non-iterable object (or array) into a single element iterator. See wrap(Object[]) for that.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type returned by the Iterator.
        Parameters:
        o - An object we would like to try and convert to an Iterator.
        Returns:
        An iterator that walks over the elements in o, or null if we cannot convert o to an Iterator.
